And that's it: call вҺ•DLX to get the solution(s). In general all problems that
can be solved by вҺ•DLX contain 3 steps:

@itemize @bullet
@item translate the problem into a constraints matrix B,
@item ZвҶҗвҺ•DLX B, and
@item translate the result Z back into the problem domain.
@end itemize

Another application of вҺ•DLX is solving sudokus. The constraints matrix is
a little more complicated, but the principle is the same. GNU APL is shipped
with two workspaces: sudoku.apl (which solves sudokus without using вҺ•DLX) and
sudoku_DLX.apl (which solves sudokus using вҺ•DLX).

