@subsection XML Queries

The different functions in dyadic вҺ•XML are intended to construct XML queries.
An XML query extracts information from, or modifies information in, an XML
document. XML queries may differ considerably in their details, but usually
follow these top-level steps:

@enumerate
@item Read an XML document into, say, APL (APLвҶҗ0 вҺ•XML B or APLвҶҗ1 вҺ•XML B)
@item Optionally, display the structure of the document (3, 4, or 5 вҺ•XML)
@item Select a subset of XML nodes (= GNU APL member names, 6 вҺ•XML APL)
@item retrieve or modify the data in the selected XML nodes
 (with something like MEMBERSвҶҗ(вҠӮAPL) FUNВЁ6вҺ•XML APLвҶҗвҺ•XML followed by MEMBERвҠғ )
@item Optionally, convert the modified XML document back to XML (0 вҺ•XML
@end enumerate

